          management. NLN is independent and not tied to any bank or investment bank although we work closely with a few
          we consider to be the best. NLN’s focus is to help a select number of very wealthy families with the design and implementation of their investment strategy.
          </p>
          <p class="grey-text text-darken-3 lighten-3" id="fontFamily">
           NLN are already supported by a couple of wealthy families, which means that at any one time we have $500m of liquid assets
          at our disposal to invest alongside our clients.
          </p>
          <p class="grey-text text-darken-3 lighten-3" id="fontFamily">
             I view the firm as a “Wealth Accelerator” rather than a Multi Family Office or Wealth Manager. Multi Family Offices often
            undertake the investment and invest with specialist firms incurring a double fee. I do not believe in this approach
            and introduce clients direct to the best of breed firms in each space. The large backing that I already have
            from wealthy families means that NLN will be significant clients for its recommended firms and will be able to
            negotiate institutional type fees. In effect, the cost of using NLN will be offset by how much better a rate
            NLN can get for the client, so the firm's services for wealthy families are in effect free.
          </p>
          <p class="grey-text text-darken-3 lighten-3" id="fontFamily">
            NLN is not in the retail client space and only work with sophisticated clients such as wealthy families and their investment
            offices and CEOs of companies. NLN also works with the entrepreneur founders of fast growing companies prior to their liquidity
            event.
          </p>
          <p class="grey-text text-darken-3 lighten-3" id="fontFamily">
            Whilst the network is naturally biased towards the twenty years I spent in Morgan Stanley’s equity business in Europe, well
            over half the network are individuals from other firms that I got to know along the way.
